  "texts": [
    "In asset protection, this task is performed by circuit breakers controlled by protection relays.",
    "They isolate areas or problematic elements on the circuit.",
    "These actions can be divided into two groups: primary and back-up.",
    "Primary protection isolates the faulty equipment with exceptional speed and precision, while backup protection acts as fail-safe, clearing faults missed by the primary system.",
    "Backup protection is slower, but covers a wider area, and its settings must be carefully calibrated to adapt to varying system conditions (Phadke et al., 2016)."
  ],
